		"description": "<p>As a bonus action, you can spend one of your artifact&rsquo;s charges and speak aloud a magic phrase or press a hidden button on your object of power to trigger a transformation into your torchbearer form. Your torch bearer form may resemble the original wielder, a stronger version of yourself, some form of magical or enhanced version of you, or it may simply constitute a wardrobe change into a uniform or outfit worn by ancient and powerful forces. Once you first select your torch bearer form, it cannot be changed.</p>\n<p>While in your torchbearer form:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You gain an expertise die on attack rolls and saving throws.</li>\n<li>You have advantage on Persuasion and Intimidation checks.</li>\n<li>Your movement speed increases by 10 feet.</li>\n<li>Beginning at level 5, whenever you take the attack action while in your torchbearer form, you may make one basic maneuver in addition to your attacks. The basic maneuver does not benefit from bonus Strength damage, but otherwise functions normally.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Whenever you begin your turn in your Torch Bearer form, you automatically spend your choice of either 2 exertion points, 2 artifact charges, or 1 exertion point and 1 artiact charge, and you revert to your normal form if you have insufficient remaining exertion points or artifact charges to spend. You can also revert into your normal form as a bonus action, and you revert automatically if killed or knocked unconscious. Any clothing you are wearing merges into your new form. Clothing that merges with you retains its effects and features.</p>",
